    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2011 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This power unit features individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio, delivering linear power delivery up to its 8,400 RPM redline. The drivetrain is equipped with the 7-speed M-DCT dual-clutch transmission, offering crisp shifts and Drivelogic adjustability. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including the replacement of rod bearings with treated shells and new connecting rod bolts to ensure long-term rotational integrity. The chassis features Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and a Variable M Differential Lock, providing superior lateral grip and turn-in precision. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina consistent with regular use, the structural rigidity and powertrain synchronization remain excellent. This is a visceral, analog experience for the enthusiast who prioritizes engineering over aesthetics.",
      "price": 33500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
